<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 6:52PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT ALLEGHANY...SOUTHWESTERN
BATH...NORTHWESTERN BOTETOURT COUNTIES IN WEST CENTRAL VIRGINIA AND
EAST CENTRAL GREENBRIER COUNTIES IN SOUTHEASTERN WEST VIRGINIA AND
THE CITY OF COVINGTON...
At 652 PM EDT, a shower was located over Callaghan, or near
Covington, moving east at 20 mph.
Winds in excess of 30 mph are possible with this shower.
Locations impacted include...
Covington...
Clifton Forge...
Neola...
Hot Springs...
Jordan Mines...
Iron Gate...
and Lake Moomaw.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
